children.text: This ensuite bathroom is deemed to be a wet area by the NCC’s Building Code of Australia, and as such, must be properly waterproofed in accordance with Australian Standard AS 3740 to prevent water leaks into the structure that could cause damage.
Part 3.8.1.2 of the Building Code of Australia (NCC/BCA) - Wet Areas, states that;
‘Building elements in wet areas within a building must-
a) be waterproof or water resistant in accordance with Table 3.8.1.1; and
Table 3.8.1.1 in the NCC/BCA shows that the area outside shower must be waterproofed;
The builder must install waterproofing to all of the wet areas of this home as required by the NCC’s Building Code of Australia and Australian Standard AS 3740.
